@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Xphere" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher and a Workbench with at least
8 colours.

                             How to play?

  To play, just click in the general direction you want to move the
sphere... if it is located at a position where a diagonal arrow
pointing either toward the front (to the lower left) or back (to
the upper right) is shown. Click diagonally from the arrow and the
display will change the labyrinth 'plane'. Note that you can use
the numeric keys of the keypad in order to mave about in the game
(8 = up, 4 = left, 6 = right and 2 = down). The '1' and '9' keys
are used to change the labyrinth plane according to the direction
shown on the diagonal arrows; '1' goes to the lower left,
corresponding to a move to the front, while '9' goes to the upper
right, corresponding to a move to the back.

    When the sphere is moving around in the game area, some objects
(pyramids, cubes and hourglass shapes) may randomly appear on the
path, if you pick one of these objects (by touching them), you get
points according to the shape of the object (a pyramid gives 1
point, a cube gives 10 points and an hourglass gives 1000 points).

  Icons of arrows, displayed at the right of the game board give a
general idea of where the sphere is located in the labyrinth planes.
In other words the arrows show if there are labyrinth planes in
front or in back. If only one arrow appear, this tells that the
sphere is located in the frontmost or rearmost labyrinth plane of
the game zone.

  The goal is to get to the exit platform (conveniently indicated
by the 'EXIT' word), which is located at the other end of the game
zone, in the least amount of moves... while making a maximum of
points!

  Click on the 'New Game' button to restart the game.

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

